This is a simulation of Rock paper scissors game

The java program is developed in such a way to satisfy the following conditions

Build a game in which two players compete in a game of Rock-Paper-Scissors with different
strategies. Who will win more rounds? The rules:
 Scissors beats Paper
 Rock beat Scissors
 Paper beats Rock
 If both players choose the same, the round is counted as a tie.
Implement two players:
 Player A always chooses Paper
 Player B chooses randomly
The game consists of 100 rounds of above two players competing. The output of the program
should be like the following:
"Player A wins 31 of 100 games"
"Player B wins 37 of 100 games"
"Tie: 32 of 100 games"


To run the program following steps needs to be done

1. Download the jar file rps-demo-0.0.2-SNAPSHOT.jar
2. Make sure that java 8 is installed in your system
3. Make sure that JAVA_HOME is set
4. then open the command line
5. Go to the folder where you have downloaded the jar file
6. Then execute the below command
   java -jar rps-demo-0.0.2-SNAPSHOT.jar

The results will be shown accordingly based on the logic Player A always chooses Paper and Player B Chooses randomly.
